1
00:00:52,260 --> 00:00:56,014
вҖӘSPOOKY IN LOVE

2
00:01:10,779 --> 00:01:14,115
вҖӘThey parked by Haedam Reservoir
вҖӘfor two hours,

3
00:01:14,199 --> 00:01:16,534
вҖӘthen drove seven kilometers
вҖӘpast the tollgate.

4
00:01:16,618 --> 00:01:18,286
вҖӘAt 1 a.m.,

5
00:01:18,369 --> 00:01:20,538
вҖӘthe missing person's phone
вҖӘwas turned off

6
00:01:20,622 --> 00:01:23,166
вҖӘsomewhere around Sanggok-myeon, soвҖҰ

7
00:01:34,969 --> 00:01:35,804
вҖӘYes?

8
00:01:37,013 --> 00:01:37,847
вҖӘWhere?

9
00:01:49,025 --> 00:01:49,901
вҖӘWho's there?

10
00:02:04,541 --> 00:02:05,416
вҖӘIt was a woman?

11
00:02:06,918 --> 00:02:07,752
вҖӘSo it's you.

12
00:02:07,836 --> 00:02:10,213
вҖӘThey say the culprit
вҖӘalways returns to the scene.

13
00:02:11,548 --> 00:02:14,092
вҖӘNo woman could dump a corpse here alone.

14
00:02:14,884 --> 00:02:15,718
вҖӘAn accomplice?

15
00:02:16,553 --> 00:02:17,679
вҖӘAre you here for this?

16
00:02:18,221 --> 00:02:19,973
вҖӘThe victim's phone? Put it down.

17
00:02:21,182 --> 00:02:22,475
вҖӘPut it down.

18
00:02:22,559 --> 00:02:23,518
вҖӘThat'sвҖҰ

19
00:02:27,522 --> 00:02:28,356
вҖӘDamn it.

20
00:02:55,425 --> 00:02:58,469
вҖӘPeople like you exhaust me.

21
00:02:58,553 --> 00:03:01,472
вҖӘPeople like you are the reason
вҖӘI have no time to be exhausted.

22
00:03:07,687 --> 00:03:09,564
вҖӘThe law is a luxury for the likes of you.

23
00:03:12,734 --> 00:03:14,152
вҖӘYou're lecturing me about the law?

24
00:03:14,235 --> 00:03:16,195
вҖӘ-What a joke.
вҖӘ-Let me go.

25
00:03:18,907 --> 00:03:20,658
вҖӘ-What do you think--
вҖӘ-Freeze.

26
00:03:20,742 --> 00:03:21,576
вҖӘDon't move!

27
00:03:25,622 --> 00:03:27,332
вҖӘWhat are you doing here this late?

28
00:03:34,672 --> 00:03:37,842
вҖӘMy gosh,
вҖӘI get that it's dark and secluded here,

29
00:03:37,926 --> 00:03:40,261
вҖӘbut aren't you being too frisky?

30
00:03:43,056 --> 00:03:44,682
вҖӘ-It's not what you think!
вҖӘ-It's not what you think!

31
00:03:45,767 --> 00:03:46,601
вҖӘDarn it.

32
00:03:48,436 --> 00:03:51,105
вҖӘGood job, guys. You can go on home now.

33
00:03:58,863 --> 00:04:00,240
вҖӘDon't touch me.

34
00:04:00,323 --> 00:04:01,991
вҖӘI'll sue you for aggravated assault.

35
00:04:02,867 --> 00:04:06,329
вҖӘIf nudging you is aggravated assault,
вҖӘwhat will you call your kick?

36
00:04:06,412 --> 00:04:09,332
вҖӘYou appeared out of nowhere
вҖӘand acted all weird.

37
00:04:09,415 --> 00:04:11,584
вҖӘYou're the weirdest one here, okay?

38
00:04:12,126 --> 00:04:15,129
вҖӘWhy were you here this late,
вҖӘand how did you know the body was here?

39
00:04:16,756 --> 00:04:18,508
вҖӘ-Well?
вҖӘ-Prosecutor Ma.

40
00:04:20,760 --> 00:04:21,636
вҖӘHey.

41
00:04:21,719 --> 00:04:23,596
вҖӘSo how did you knowвҖҰ

42
00:04:25,556 --> 00:04:27,267
вҖӘWhat the heck? Where'd she go?

43
00:04:27,350 --> 00:04:28,393
вҖӘWhat? Who?

44
00:04:28,893 --> 00:04:31,187
вҖӘ-Where didвҖҰ
вҖӘ-Who? What?

45
00:04:31,271 --> 00:04:34,524
вҖӘDidn't you see the woman
вҖӘI was just talking to?

46
00:04:34,607 --> 00:04:36,442
вҖӘWhat woman?
вҖӘCome on, you're scaring me.

47
00:04:36,526 --> 00:04:38,027
вҖӘShe was in a hoodie.

48
00:04:38,111 --> 00:04:39,988
вҖӘCome on, now. You must've seen a ghost.

49
00:04:40,071 --> 00:04:43,324
вҖӘThis is why I told you
вҖӘto go to bed on time.

50
00:04:44,367 --> 00:04:47,120
вҖӘBut she was standing right here
вҖӘa minute ago.

51
00:04:47,954 --> 00:04:49,455
вҖӘYeah, sure.

52
00:04:49,539 --> 00:04:52,250
вҖӘSo how did the caller know
вҖӘthe body was here?

53
00:04:54,043 --> 00:04:56,045
вҖӘWho called in the tip-off?

54
00:05:07,348 --> 00:05:11,644
вҖӘI know you're angry
вҖӘit took so long to find your body,

55
00:05:12,228 --> 00:05:14,355
вҖӘbut the killer will pay.

56
00:05:16,065 --> 00:05:17,525
вҖӘSo let it all go and move on.

57
00:05:19,027 --> 00:05:22,280
вҖӘAnd marry a good person in your next life.

58
00:05:27,493 --> 00:05:29,620
вҖӘIs there even a next life?

59
00:05:30,955 --> 00:05:33,750
вҖӘI think my current life
вҖӘis royally screwed.

60
00:05:34,459 --> 00:05:36,794
вҖӘIf I were told I could get a second try

61
00:05:37,628 --> 00:05:39,005
вҖӘat living again, perhapsвҖҰ

62
00:05:40,173 --> 00:05:42,425
вҖӘWait. Where'd he go?

63
00:05:43,426 --> 00:05:44,802
вҖӘYou moved on already?

64
00:05:45,845 --> 00:05:48,014
вҖӘCouldn't you give me an answer first?

65
00:05:48,097 --> 00:05:50,600
вҖӘWhy do they all vanish
вҖӘwhenever I ask them that?

66
00:05:50,683 --> 00:05:53,561
вҖӘAren't we on the same side?
вҖӘWe have a camaraderie.

67
00:05:54,771 --> 00:05:55,772
вҖӘDon't we?

68
00:05:58,399 --> 00:05:59,358
вҖӘI guess we don't.

69
00:06:10,369 --> 00:06:11,370
вҖӘYeo-ri.

70
00:06:13,623 --> 00:06:15,875
вҖӘ6 YEARS AGO

71
00:06:20,338 --> 00:06:22,757
вҖӘWhat's the matter? You don't like it?

72
00:06:23,466 --> 00:06:25,384
вҖӘAre you really okay with this?

73
00:06:25,468 --> 00:06:27,637
вҖӘFor as long as you're with me,

74
00:06:27,720 --> 00:06:30,932
вҖӘyou'll live with fear and horror.

75
00:06:32,725 --> 00:06:35,269
вҖӘThey'll become a part of your life.

76
00:06:36,813 --> 00:06:38,189
вҖӘI heard all about that.

77
00:06:41,234 --> 00:06:42,110
вҖӘGive me your hand.

78
00:06:56,707 --> 00:06:57,625
вҖӘIt's fine.

79
00:06:58,417 --> 00:06:59,418
вҖӘNothing will happen.

80
00:07:31,284 --> 00:07:32,910
<i>вҖӘNext, we have some business news.</i>

81
00:07:32,994 --> 00:07:37,790
<i>вҖӘCheon Yeo-ri,</i>
<i>вҖӘthe Reina Hotels & Resorts heiress</i>

82
00:07:37,874 --> 00:07:40,293
<i>вҖӘand Cha Gi-u, the eldest son</i>
<i>вҖӘof Cha & Yul Law Firm's partner</i>

83
00:07:40,376 --> 00:07:42,044
<i>вҖӘare to be engaged today.</i>

84
00:07:42,712 --> 00:07:43,838
<i>вҖӘThey met early in the year</i>

85
00:07:43,921 --> 00:07:47,592
<i>вҖӘthrough a mutual friend,</i>
<i>вҖӘand dated with prospects of marriage.</i>

86
00:07:47,675 --> 00:07:51,262
<i>вҖӘThe union of two prestigious business</i>

87
00:07:51,345 --> 00:07:54,140
<i>вҖӘand legal entities has everyone talking.</i>

88
00:07:54,223 --> 00:07:57,977
<i>вҖӘThe engagement will be held in private</i>
<i>вҖӘat Reina Hotel's Siena Hall.</i>

89
00:08:03,357 --> 00:08:08,529
вҖӘCHEON YEO-RI & CHA GI-U

90
00:08:24,045 --> 00:08:25,004
вҖӘI'm so sorry.

91
00:08:25,796 --> 00:08:28,007
вҖӘI left home early,
вҖӘbut the traffic was insane.

92
00:08:29,383 --> 00:08:30,468
вҖӘIt's okay, you're here now.

93
00:08:31,052 --> 00:08:33,387
вҖӘEveryone's waiting. We should go.

94
00:08:34,972 --> 00:08:36,432
вҖӘYou look amazing today.

95
00:08:37,266 --> 00:08:38,100
вҖӘLet's go.

96
00:08:41,979 --> 00:08:43,356
вҖӘThe engagement ring.

97
00:08:43,439 --> 00:08:44,690
вҖӘI must've left it in the car.

98
00:08:46,317 --> 00:08:47,568
вҖӘI'll be right back.

99
00:09:07,213 --> 00:09:08,047
вҖӘWhat's happening?

100
00:09:45,918 --> 00:09:47,920
вҖӘHey. Get a hold of yourself.

101
00:09:58,889 --> 00:09:59,724
вҖӘHello?

102
00:09:59,807 --> 00:10:01,976
вҖӘThe elevator's flooding!

103
00:10:02,560 --> 00:10:05,646
вҖӘHello? The elevator's flooded!

104
00:10:07,148 --> 00:10:08,065
вҖӘHello?

105
00:10:09,066 --> 00:10:09,900
вҖӘDamn it.

106
00:10:52,943 --> 00:10:54,195
вҖӘGi-u.

107
00:10:54,278 --> 00:10:56,197
вҖӘ-Are you all right?
вҖӘ-Don't come closer.

108
00:10:56,989 --> 00:10:58,908
вҖӘ-Gi-u.
вҖӘ-Stay right there!

109
00:11:01,035 --> 00:11:03,079
вҖӘI didn't think I'd actually become haunted

110
00:11:03,954 --> 00:11:05,665
вҖӘjust by holding your hand.

111
00:11:11,796 --> 00:11:12,713
вҖӘYeo-ri.

112
00:11:14,090 --> 00:11:15,007
вҖӘI'm sorry.

113
00:11:15,716 --> 00:11:17,843
вҖӘI don't think I can marry you. I'm sorry.

114
00:11:29,271 --> 00:11:30,689
вҖӘI won't date her.

115
00:11:30,773 --> 00:11:32,566
вҖӘI won't ever see Yeo-ri again.

116
00:11:51,293 --> 00:11:52,795
<i>вҖӘThat's when I realizedвҖҰ</i>

117
00:11:55,005 --> 00:11:58,050
<i>вҖӘthat I couldn't touch anyone ever </i><i>вҖӘagain.</i>

118
00:12:03,514 --> 00:12:05,474
<i>вҖӘThat I shouldn't rely on</i>

119
00:12:06,225 --> 00:12:07,810
<i>вҖӘor expect anything from anyone.</i>

120
00:12:11,647 --> 00:12:12,940
<i>вҖӘThat's when I also decidedвҖҰ</i>

121
00:12:14,859 --> 00:12:17,486
<i>вҖӘthat if I couldn't avoid the spirits</i>
<i>вҖӘthat came to find me,</i>

122
00:12:19,238 --> 00:12:21,073
<i>вҖӘthen I'd learn not to let them bother me.</i>

123
00:12:24,743 --> 00:12:26,287
<i>вҖӘI may not be welcoming,</i>

124
00:12:28,789 --> 00:12:31,500
<i>вҖӘbut I'd try to overcome it </i><i>вҖӘenough</i>
<i>вҖӘthat I wouldn't fear</i>

125
00:12:33,377 --> 00:12:34,712
<i>вҖӘbeing around them.</i>

126
00:12:38,799 --> 00:12:42,511
вҖӘSPOOKY IN LOVE

127
00:12:43,387 --> 00:12:45,222
вҖӘEPISODE 1

128
00:13:16,837 --> 00:13:18,464
вҖӘThe whole point of this case is

129
00:13:18,964 --> 00:13:21,675
вҖӘthat although the parties
вҖӘdo seem to be connected,

130
00:13:21,759 --> 00:13:23,928
вҖӘthere's only circumstantial evidence

131
00:13:24,011 --> 00:13:26,764
вҖӘand no direct evidence
вҖӘsuch as a corpse or murder weapon.

132
00:13:27,598 --> 00:13:30,309
<i>вҖӘWe uphold </i><i>вҖӘthe </i><i>вҖӘprinciple </i><i>вҖӘof </i><i>вҖӘtrial</i>
<i>вҖӘby evidence,</i>

133
00:13:31,227 --> 00:13:34,313
<i>вҖӘand therefore have concluded</i>
<i>вҖӘthere's not enough</i>

134
00:13:34,396 --> 00:13:36,524
вҖӘto result in a conviction.

135
00:13:39,151 --> 00:13:41,070
вҖӘDefendant, please rise.

136
00:13:43,572 --> 00:13:47,201
вҖӘCase No. 5410-Badan-1651.

137
00:13:47,284 --> 00:13:48,494
вҖӘThe sentence.

138
00:13:48,577 --> 00:13:52,540
вҖӘDefendant Park Seung-jae,
вҖӘaccused of the murder of Jang Eun-ju.

139
00:13:52,623 --> 00:13:54,583
вҖӘWe find him not guilty.

140
00:13:55,125 --> 00:13:58,879
вҖӘ-What? Not guilty?
вҖӘ-This trial is concluded.

141
00:14:02,633 --> 00:14:04,885
вҖӘGood job. Well done, man.

142
00:14:04,969 --> 00:14:05,928
вҖӘYou did great.

143
00:14:19,441 --> 00:14:21,068
вҖӘHow does it feel to lose?

144
00:14:21,652 --> 00:14:22,695
вҖӘI'll appeal.

145
00:14:23,487 --> 00:14:25,573
вҖӘThey say there's no hope for the stupid.

146
00:14:25,656 --> 00:14:27,157
вҖӘDid you forget what the judge said?

147
00:14:27,241 --> 00:14:29,535
вҖӘIt's trial by evidence
вҖӘand you have no body.

148
00:14:29,618 --> 00:14:32,621
вҖӘBring material evidence,
вҖӘnot circumstantial nonsense.

149
00:14:33,873 --> 00:14:35,916
вҖӘNo evidence now
вҖӘdoesn't mean no evidence forever.

150
00:14:36,000 --> 00:14:39,253
вҖӘI'll find something before the appeal
вҖӘand lock you up.

151
00:14:39,336 --> 00:14:41,171
вҖӘ-By the book.
вҖӘ-Sure, whatever.

152
00:14:41,255 --> 00:14:42,715
вҖӘWhatever helps you sleep at night.

153
00:14:42,798 --> 00:14:44,049
вҖӘYou follow your dear law.

154
00:14:44,758 --> 00:14:46,010
вҖӘI'll do whatever I want.

155
00:14:53,517 --> 00:14:54,643
вҖӘProsecutor Ma.

156
00:14:59,398 --> 00:15:01,525
вҖӘCHIEF PROSECUTOR NAM SANG-HO

157
00:15:06,822 --> 00:15:07,781
вҖӘWhat will you do?

158
00:15:08,365 --> 00:15:09,742
вҖӘType out a cause for appeal.

159
00:15:10,492 --> 00:15:14,038
вҖӘOver a drop of blood on his shirt
вҖӘwhen you don't have a body?

160
00:15:15,789 --> 00:15:17,833
вҖӘPlease, Gang-ukвҖҰ

161
00:15:17,917 --> 00:15:20,294
вҖӘYou won't talk me out of appealing,
вҖӘwill you?

162
00:15:20,377 --> 00:15:22,379
вҖӘPark Seung-jae's father,
вҖӘAssemblyman Park Jin-dong

163
00:15:22,463 --> 00:15:24,548
вҖӘis the ruling party's
вҖӘlikely presidential candidate.

164
00:15:25,049 --> 00:15:26,634
вҖӘI already have my orders from above.

165
00:15:26,717 --> 00:15:28,302
вҖӘIt's time to drop it.

166
00:15:28,385 --> 00:15:29,887
вҖӘCan't you back me up even a little?

167
00:15:29,970 --> 00:15:30,846
вҖӘI don'tвҖҰ

168
00:15:31,680 --> 00:15:33,807
вҖӘI really don't want to be petty
вҖӘand say this--

169
00:15:33,891 --> 00:15:37,102
вҖӘNot a word then.
вҖӘI'll recite your usual spiel.

170
00:15:37,186 --> 00:15:38,771
вҖӘThe Daebak Savings Bank corruption case.

171
00:15:38,854 --> 00:15:40,940
вҖӘThe YOLO City fraudulent estate sale case.

172
00:15:41,023 --> 00:15:41,857
вҖӘThat's not all.

173
00:15:41,941 --> 00:15:44,652
вҖӘThe Seojin Construction
вҖӘpolitical bribery case.

174
00:15:44,735 --> 00:15:45,861
вҖӘDespite immense outside pressure,

175
00:15:45,945 --> 00:15:49,281
вҖӘyou indicted them all and took them
вҖӘto court without batting an eyelid.

176
00:15:49,365 --> 00:15:50,199
вҖӘOn top of that,

177
00:15:50,282 --> 00:15:53,911
вҖӘyou maintained your stance
вҖӘand scored hefty penalties for them all.

178
00:15:55,204 --> 00:15:58,207
вҖӘYou crazy bastard.
вҖӘYou did all that on your own.

179
00:15:58,290 --> 00:16:02,044
вҖӘYou did all the work
вҖӘand I took all the credit.

180
00:16:02,127 --> 00:16:03,045
вҖӘI admit that too.

181
00:16:03,128 --> 00:16:04,630
вҖӘBut Gang-ukвҖҰ

182
00:16:04,713 --> 00:16:07,132
вҖӘForget everything else.
вҖӘLet me work according to the law.

183
00:16:08,133 --> 00:16:09,134
вҖӘOh, goshвҖҰ

184
00:16:10,344 --> 00:16:12,638
вҖӘMan, my eyes hurt bad.

185
00:16:12,721 --> 00:16:14,056
вҖӘCRIMINAL PROSECUTION 12,
вҖӘCHIEF PROSECUTOR'S OFFICE

186
00:16:16,100 --> 00:16:17,267
вҖӘWhat will you do now?

187
00:16:17,351 --> 00:16:18,435
вҖӘGiving upвҖҰ

188
00:16:19,103 --> 00:16:20,980
вҖӘis not an option. We should fight.

189
00:16:21,522 --> 00:16:22,940
вҖӘ-Excuse me.
вҖӘ-Sure.

190
00:16:24,149 --> 00:16:25,567
вҖӘMADAM PANG

191
00:16:25,651 --> 00:16:27,027
вҖӘWhy is Madam Pang calling?

192
00:16:28,320 --> 00:16:29,154
вҖӘHello?

193
00:16:30,739 --> 00:16:32,491
вҖӘOh, that's today?

194
00:16:32,574 --> 00:16:36,245
вҖӘI'm a bit busy.
вҖӘDoes the monk do remote prayersвҖҰ

195
00:16:40,624 --> 00:16:41,625
вҖӘCould you go instead?

196
00:16:42,292 --> 00:16:46,672
вҖӘYou see, I'm considering going to church.

197
00:16:46,755 --> 00:16:48,048
вҖӘI think it's best if you go.

198
00:17:00,769 --> 00:17:01,603
вҖӘGrandma.

199
00:17:01,687 --> 00:17:03,856
вҖӘDo it properly, with all your heart.

200
00:17:16,869 --> 00:17:19,621
вҖӘHow much longer do I have to keep this up?

201
00:17:20,748 --> 00:17:21,665
вҖӘHello, Venerable.

202
00:17:24,877 --> 00:17:27,379
вҖӘYou just do as you're told.

203
00:17:27,463 --> 00:17:29,590
вҖӘI'm not saying I won't attend the service.

204
00:17:29,673 --> 00:17:32,259
вҖӘAt least tell me who I'm praying for
вҖӘso I can--

205
00:17:32,342 --> 00:17:33,177
вҖӘEnough.

206
00:17:36,221 --> 00:17:38,557
вҖӘMadam Pang, I have a hunch.

207
00:17:38,640 --> 00:17:40,642
вҖӘ-Is the person I'm praying for--
вҖӘ-Right.

208
00:17:41,685 --> 00:17:44,521
вҖӘI spoke to the chief monk already,

209
00:17:44,605 --> 00:17:47,024
вҖӘ-so pay the temple office.
вҖӘ-Yes, ma'am.

210
00:17:48,567 --> 00:17:49,443
вҖӘOh, right.

211
00:17:49,526 --> 00:17:51,779
вҖӘI'll say it again, for your sake.

212
00:17:51,862 --> 00:17:55,115
вҖӘYou must stay well away from women
вҖӘborn in the year of the Black Monkey.

213
00:17:55,199 --> 00:17:56,283
вҖӘAll right?

214
00:17:57,201 --> 00:18:01,080
вҖӘBlack Monkey or White Monkey,
вҖӘI don't have the time to meet anyone.

215
00:18:01,163 --> 00:18:03,082
вҖӘWhat zodiac signs
вҖӘare you incompatible with?

216
00:18:03,624 --> 00:18:04,583
вҖӘWhy do you ask?

217
00:18:04,666 --> 00:18:06,502
вҖӘJust so I know.

218
00:18:06,585 --> 00:18:11,632
вҖӘWe can't have you meeting your soulmate
вҖӘonly to find out you're incompatible.

219
00:18:11,715 --> 00:18:12,674
вҖӘYou darn fool.

220
00:18:12,758 --> 00:18:14,301
вҖӘYou can't talk like that at a temple.

221
00:18:14,802 --> 00:18:16,804
вҖӘ-We're leaving.
вҖӘ-Come on, it's harmless fun.

222
00:18:17,679 --> 00:18:19,473
вҖӘYou're too cheeky for your own good.

223
00:18:19,556 --> 00:18:22,184
вҖӘWhat happened to the old man from before?

224
00:18:22,267 --> 00:18:23,852
вҖӘ-Who?
вҖӘ-It seemed to be going well.

225
00:18:23,936 --> 00:18:25,479
вҖӘYou crazy fool.

226
00:18:36,281 --> 00:18:38,033
вҖӘOh, welcome.

227
00:18:39,868 --> 00:18:41,370
вҖӘWhere to, sir?

228
00:18:42,412 --> 00:18:43,247
вҖӘSir?

229
00:18:52,965 --> 00:18:54,174
вҖӘAren't you going home?

230
00:18:56,009 --> 00:18:58,595
вҖӘYou won't stay on the Jang Eun-ju case,
вҖӘwill you?

231
00:18:58,679 --> 00:19:00,806
вҖӘNot you too, Investigator Ko.

232
00:19:00,889 --> 00:19:03,684
вҖӘI mean, it's raining hard.

233
00:19:03,767 --> 00:19:06,854
вҖӘIt's the perfect night for a nice drink.

234
00:19:06,937 --> 00:19:09,523
вҖӘIt's raining hard,
вҖӘso why don't you just go home?

235
00:19:09,606 --> 00:19:11,608
вҖӘHave some quality time with your wife.

236
00:19:11,692 --> 00:19:15,028
вҖӘMy wife says all she wants from me
вҖӘis confirmation that I'm alive.

237
00:19:15,112 --> 00:19:17,614
вҖӘOh, dear. Is that why you're sulking?

238
00:19:17,698 --> 00:19:19,533
вҖӘWill you keep me company then?

239
00:19:20,409 --> 00:19:22,578
вҖӘI'm willing if you're buying.

240
00:19:22,661 --> 00:19:23,495
вҖӘI'm always free.

241
00:19:23,579 --> 00:19:26,290
вҖӘYou never even suggest you'll buy.

242
00:19:26,373 --> 00:19:27,833
вҖӘLet's split the bill today. 50-50.

243
00:19:27,916 --> 00:19:29,918
вҖӘ-Who pays 50?
вҖӘ-What?

244
00:19:30,961 --> 00:19:32,588
вҖӘI pay 50, of course.

245
00:19:32,671 --> 00:19:33,672
вҖӘWith our prosecutor's card.

246
00:19:33,755 --> 00:19:36,049
вҖӘYou really won't join us, sir?

247
00:19:38,427 --> 00:19:39,636
вҖӘOh, right.

248
00:19:39,720 --> 00:19:41,680
вҖӘThe bathroom light is out.

249
00:19:41,763 --> 00:19:44,641
вҖӘOh, that's right.
вҖӘDon't use the last stall.

250
00:19:44,725 --> 00:19:47,436
вҖӘ-They say a ghost appears on rainy days--
вҖӘ-Get out of here already.

251
00:19:47,519 --> 00:19:49,646
вҖӘ-Watch out.
вҖӘ-The ghost harasses people.

252
00:19:49,730 --> 00:19:51,940
вҖӘ-Don't drink too much!
вҖӘ-I'm serious.

253
00:19:55,819 --> 00:19:58,697
вҖӘKEEP THE TOILET CLEAN
вҖӘTAKE ALL YOUR BELONGINGS!

254
00:20:04,453 --> 00:20:06,955
вҖӘThis happens whenever it rains.

255
00:20:07,539 --> 00:20:08,665
вҖӘDamn it.

256
00:20:19,218 --> 00:20:20,302
вҖӘWho's there?

257
00:20:20,969 --> 00:20:23,138
<i>вҖӘDon't use the last stall.</i>

258
00:20:23,805 --> 00:20:26,642
<i>вҖӘThey say a ghost appears on rainy days.</i>

259
00:20:29,102 --> 00:20:29,978
вҖӘShow yourself!

260
00:21:42,050 --> 00:21:43,677
вҖӘOUT OF ORDER, DO NOT USE

261
00:22:05,324 --> 00:22:07,617
вҖӘWhere are we on the Jane MГјller deal?

262
00:22:08,910 --> 00:22:09,745
вҖӘYes, ma'am.

263
00:22:10,620 --> 00:22:12,956
вҖӘJane MГјller's a world-famous florist,

264
00:22:13,040 --> 00:22:15,167
вҖӘand we had some scheduling difficulties.

265
00:22:15,250 --> 00:22:17,085
вҖӘWe were finally able to arrange a meeting.

266
00:22:17,169 --> 00:22:18,670
вҖӘ-I'll organize your trip--
вҖӘ-Stop.

267
00:22:23,842 --> 00:22:24,676
вҖӘMaintain your distance.

268
00:22:30,974 --> 00:22:31,975
вҖӘI apologize, Ms. Cheon.

269
00:22:32,059 --> 00:22:34,478
вҖӘ-I got carried away with the brief.
вҖӘ-Catch me if you can.

270
00:22:49,326 --> 00:22:50,994
вҖӘSweetie, are you all right?

271
00:22:51,953 --> 00:22:52,996
вҖӘLet's get you up.

272
00:22:53,497 --> 00:22:55,499
вҖӘI'm so sorry.

273
00:22:56,166 --> 00:22:57,042
вҖӘLet's go.

274
00:23:00,962 --> 00:23:01,838
вҖӘMs. Cheon.

275
00:23:03,381 --> 00:23:04,841
вҖӘThe chairwoman is asking for you.

276
00:23:07,094 --> 00:23:09,596
вҖӘ-Here he comes.
вҖӘ-How do you feel right now?

277
00:23:09,679 --> 00:23:11,890
вҖӘ-Any comments?
вҖӘ-What do you have to say?

278
00:23:11,973 --> 00:23:13,350
вҖӘ-How do you feel?
вҖӘ-Anything to say?

279
00:23:13,433 --> 00:23:15,268
вҖӘ-Look at the cameras.
вҖӘ-Pose for some photos.

280
00:23:16,603 --> 00:23:20,107
вҖӘFirst of all, I respect
вҖӘthe judiciary's sensible decision.

281
00:23:20,899 --> 00:23:23,568
вҖӘI'm pleased the truth came out
вҖӘbefore it was too late.

282
00:23:24,528 --> 00:23:27,864
<i>вҖӘI thank everyone who believed in me</i>
<i>вҖӘand waited for the verdict.</i>

283
00:23:27,948 --> 00:23:30,826
<i>вҖӘI'll do a full interview at a later date.</i>

284
00:23:30,909 --> 00:23:32,327
<i>вҖӘAre you satisfied with the verdict?</i>

285
00:23:32,410 --> 00:23:33,578
<i>вҖӘHow will your career--</i>

286
00:23:37,249 --> 00:23:38,583
вҖӘHe was found not guilty.

287
00:23:39,626 --> 00:23:41,294
вҖӘCan I go ahead and marry him?

288
00:23:41,378 --> 00:23:43,839
вҖӘNegligence and embezzlement

289
00:23:43,922 --> 00:23:46,341
вҖӘcome with the territory
вҖӘwhen you're in business,

290
00:23:46,424 --> 00:23:49,344
вҖӘbut aren't you concerned
вҖӘhe was charged with murder?

291
00:23:49,427 --> 00:23:50,554
вҖӘNo, Chairwoman.

292
00:23:51,972 --> 00:23:53,765
вҖӘCome on, Grandma.

293
00:23:53,849 --> 00:23:56,893
вҖӘThat brat clung to him like superglue,

294
00:23:56,977 --> 00:23:59,229
вҖӘthen went into hiding
вҖӘwhen she couldn't get her way.

295
00:24:00,230 --> 00:24:02,858
вҖӘIf you think about it,
вҖӘSeung-jae's a victim too.

296
00:24:03,984 --> 00:24:05,819
вҖӘIt's not just about marriage.

297
00:24:06,444 --> 00:24:08,864
вҖӘIt involves business interests too.

298
00:24:10,115 --> 00:24:13,535
вҖӘOur new resort needs building approval
вҖӘand it's in his father's constituency.

299
00:24:13,618 --> 00:24:14,578
вҖӘPostponing the wedding

300
00:24:14,661 --> 00:24:17,205
вҖӘmight only delay our business plans.

301
00:24:26,715 --> 00:24:28,633
вҖӘWe were discussing Ha-ri's marriage.

302
00:24:30,051 --> 00:24:32,429
вҖӘI asked you to join
вҖӘbecause we haven't met in a while.

303
00:24:33,013 --> 00:24:35,599
вҖӘWhat do you think
вҖӘabout Assemblyman Park's son?

304
00:24:36,641 --> 00:24:39,477
вҖӘDoes it matter what I think?
вҖӘHa-ri's the one getting married.

305
00:24:39,561 --> 00:24:41,396
вҖӘOf course your opinion matters.

306
00:24:41,479 --> 00:24:43,273
вҖӘOur family is an economic unit.

307
00:24:44,566 --> 00:24:47,194
вҖӘIf we're an economic unit,
вҖӘthe wedding should happen.

308
00:24:50,697 --> 00:24:52,699
вҖӘThat's your stance as an older cousin.

309
00:24:52,782 --> 00:24:54,826
вҖӘWhat do you think as a big sister?

310
00:24:54,910 --> 00:24:57,495
вҖӘIf you want my opinion as a big sisterвҖҰ

311
00:24:59,915 --> 00:25:02,584
вҖӘI'll never accept a parasite like him.

312
00:25:04,336 --> 00:25:06,254
вҖӘYou called him a parasite?

313
00:25:06,922 --> 00:25:08,506
вҖӘIsn't that a bit too harsh?

314
00:25:08,590 --> 00:25:10,258
вҖӘIf Mr. Park's a parasite,

315
00:25:10,342 --> 00:25:12,093
вҖӘdo you think his father is a host?

316
00:25:12,594 --> 00:25:14,346
вҖӘI don't like the sound of that.

317
00:25:15,430 --> 00:25:18,058
вҖӘI know you're just cousins,
вҖӘbut you grew up together.

318
00:25:18,141 --> 00:25:21,144
вҖӘI say that because we grew up together.

319
00:25:21,686 --> 00:25:24,814
вҖӘTo be honest,
вҖӘwithout his assemblyman father,

320
00:25:25,315 --> 00:25:26,274
вҖӘMr. Park has nothing to offer.

321
00:25:27,150 --> 00:25:29,569
вҖӘHow do you feel about him
вҖӘin relation to the ruling?

322
00:25:29,653 --> 00:25:31,112
вҖӘFrankly, the whole thing started

323
00:25:31,196 --> 00:25:35,116
вҖӘbecause Park Seung-jae
вҖӘdumped Jang Eun-ju for Ha-ri.

324
00:25:36,117 --> 00:25:37,160
вҖӘHa-ri.

325
00:25:37,869 --> 00:25:38,870
вҖӘWhat's your charm?

326
00:25:39,454 --> 00:25:41,873
вҖӘYeo-ri, what kind of question is that?

327
00:25:41,957 --> 00:25:43,124
вҖӘOur Ha-riвҖҰ

328
00:25:44,042 --> 00:25:45,210
вҖӘhas her beauty.

329
00:25:45,293 --> 00:25:47,379
вҖӘYes, I was born with a noble elegance.

330
00:25:48,171 --> 00:25:49,297
вҖӘI stand to inherit loads too.

331
00:25:49,381 --> 00:25:51,341
вҖӘOnce a cheater, always a cheater.

332
00:25:51,424 --> 00:25:54,302
вҖӘIf he were to come across
вҖӘan heiress with more pull,

333
00:25:54,886 --> 00:25:56,721
вҖӘPark Seung-jae will dump you for her.

334
00:25:58,598 --> 00:26:01,851
вҖӘAre you trying to keep me in check
вҖӘin case Seung-jae helps us

335
00:26:01,935 --> 00:26:05,063
вҖӘsecure the resort license
вҖӘand boost my equity?

336
00:26:05,855 --> 00:26:07,065
вҖӘHa-ri.

337
00:26:07,148 --> 00:26:09,609
вҖӘLet's see how things play out.

338
00:26:10,694 --> 00:26:11,903
вҖӘWe'll wait and see.

339
00:26:12,696 --> 00:26:13,989
вҖӘGive me a moment, Yeo-ri.

340
00:26:15,865 --> 00:26:17,367
вҖӘThe occupation rates

341
00:26:17,867 --> 00:26:20,245
вҖӘare holding up pretty well
вҖӘconsidering it's off-season.

342
00:26:20,996 --> 00:26:23,415
вҖӘThe restaurants and banquet halls

343
00:26:23,498 --> 00:26:24,833
вҖӘare fully booked every day.

344
00:26:27,043 --> 00:26:29,004
вҖӘSiena Hall is the real problem.

345
00:26:30,380 --> 00:26:31,631
вҖӘSiena HallвҖҰ

346
00:26:31,715 --> 00:26:34,801
<i>вҖӘIt's not just a problem.</i>
<i>вҖӘIt makes zero sales.</i>

347
00:26:34,884 --> 00:26:36,886
вҖӘIt's as good as a disaster.

348
00:26:36,970 --> 00:26:38,471
вҖӘIt's not that bad.

349
00:26:38,555 --> 00:26:42,058
вҖӘIt was every couple's dream venue
вҖӘbefore the renovation.

350
00:26:42,142 --> 00:26:43,143
вҖӘIt was.

351
00:26:43,226 --> 00:26:45,979
вҖӘUntil Cheon Yeo-ri wanted to be the first
вҖӘto get engaged after the reopening,

352
00:26:46,062 --> 00:26:47,147
вҖӘand ruined everything.

353
00:26:47,230 --> 00:26:48,815
вҖӘShe ruined everything? How?

354
00:26:48,898 --> 00:26:51,776
вҖӘHer fiancГ© ran off
вҖӘright before the engagement.

355
00:26:52,444 --> 00:26:54,612
вҖӘWho'd want to marry there
вҖӘafter the first couple broke up?

356
00:26:55,530 --> 00:26:58,491
вҖӘThey say no couple
вҖӘthat got engaged or married there

357
00:26:58,575 --> 00:27:00,452
вҖӘlasted more than two years.

358
00:27:01,661 --> 00:27:05,874
вҖӘThat's how Siena Hall became
вҖӘCheon Yeo-ri's most painful weakness.

359
00:27:07,083 --> 00:27:08,626
вҖӘIt can't be great all the time.

360
00:27:09,336 --> 00:27:12,547
вҖӘApart from Siena Hall,
вҖӘour sales are the highest in the area.

361
00:27:14,007 --> 00:27:16,384
вҖӘWe couldn't have done that
вҖӘwithout Ms. Cheon.

362
00:27:17,052 --> 00:27:18,219
вҖӘThat's true.

363
00:27:18,303 --> 00:27:20,680
вҖӘI must admit, she's a great businesswoman.

364
00:27:21,598 --> 00:27:24,392
вҖӘIf only she were nicer
вҖӘto the people around herвҖҰ

365
00:27:26,853 --> 00:27:28,605
вҖӘHow long do we have to wait anyway?

366
00:27:30,315 --> 00:27:31,941
вҖӘIt'll be here soon.
вҖӘYou must be hungry.

367
00:27:32,025 --> 00:27:33,443
вҖӘI'm starving. Hurry up.

368
00:27:34,569 --> 00:27:37,405
вҖӘBy the way,
вҖӘwhat happens to Siena Hall now?

369
00:27:38,990 --> 00:27:39,991
вҖӘI don't know.

370
00:27:40,700 --> 00:27:43,286
вҖӘI guess the chairwoman
вҖӘwill make a call soon.

371
00:28:06,101 --> 00:28:08,770
вҖӘHow about we use this building
вҖӘas something else entirely?

372
00:28:08,853 --> 00:28:09,979
вҖӘAs an art gallery.

373
00:28:11,356 --> 00:28:12,190
вҖӘSiena Hall, you mean?

374
00:28:13,400 --> 00:28:15,985
вҖӘI was going to mention it
вҖӘat the strategy meeting in two days.

375
00:28:16,069 --> 00:28:18,780
вҖӘA gallery is a great idea.
вҖӘAs expected, GrandmaвҖҰ

376
00:28:18,863 --> 00:28:20,865
вҖӘChairwoman,
вҖӘI applaud your thought process.

377
00:28:21,574 --> 00:28:22,909
вҖӘMom, it's what you always wanted.

378
00:28:23,535 --> 00:28:26,329
вҖӘ-If you were to do that for meвҖҰ
вҖӘ-I can't accept that.

379
00:28:27,163 --> 00:28:29,374
вҖӘYou know what this hall means to me.

380
00:28:29,457 --> 00:28:32,752
вҖӘMy dad designed and built this place
вҖӘfor my mom.

381
00:28:33,837 --> 00:28:36,548
вҖӘIt can never be used for anything else.

382
00:28:37,549 --> 00:28:39,676
вҖӘIn any case,
вҖӘSiena Hall is still part of the hotel.

383
00:28:40,802 --> 00:28:43,012
вҖӘA building that doesn't make money
вҖӘis just an eyesore.

384
00:28:43,930 --> 00:28:45,765
вҖӘThat's what I still think and believe.

385
00:28:50,812 --> 00:28:53,773
вҖӘHow about we have dinner together
вҖӘsince it's been a while?

386
00:28:53,857 --> 00:28:54,733
вҖӘI'm sorry,

387
00:28:54,816 --> 00:28:56,901
вҖӘbut my routine is to get home before dusk.

388
00:29:37,484 --> 00:29:38,485
<i>вҖӘI didn't think</i>

389
00:29:39,611 --> 00:29:41,654
<i>вҖӘI'd actually become haunted</i>
<i>вҖӘbecause </i><i>вҖӘof </i><i>вҖӘyou.</i>

390
00:29:54,334 --> 00:29:55,919
<i>вҖӘSiena Hall is the real problem.</i>

391
00:29:56,002 --> 00:29:58,129
вҖӘHow about we use this building
вҖӘas something else entirely?

392
00:29:58,755 --> 00:29:59,923
вҖӘAs an art gallery.

393
00:31:58,625 --> 00:31:59,459
вҖӘCheers.

394
00:32:08,801 --> 00:32:11,304
вҖӘOh, gosh. Give me those.

395
00:32:11,387 --> 00:32:13,473
вҖӘWe need a steady flow of cooked meat.

396
00:32:14,182 --> 00:32:16,476
вҖӘHow many times did I tell you so?

397
00:32:16,559 --> 00:32:18,937
вҖӘCan't we eat raw fish too,
вҖӘevery once in a while?

398
00:32:19,479 --> 00:32:21,439
вҖӘWe're always eating pork skin and offal.

399
00:32:21,522 --> 00:32:22,565
вҖӘI can't take it anymore.

400
00:32:24,400 --> 00:32:26,152
вҖӘYou don't know what you're talking about.

401
00:32:27,111 --> 00:32:29,781
вҖӘThe internal organs taste best,
вҖӘHyeong-min.

402
00:32:29,864 --> 00:32:32,659
вҖӘIt's not good to eat too much food
вҖӘthat's high in fat.

403
00:32:32,742 --> 00:32:33,993
вҖӘYou need to watch your health.

404
00:32:34,077 --> 00:32:37,163
вҖӘSpeaking of which,
вҖӘhow many supplements do you take a day?

405
00:32:37,246 --> 00:32:38,957
вҖӘI used to take 12.

406
00:32:39,040 --> 00:32:41,167
вҖӘBut I started taking spirulina,
вҖӘso it's 14 now.

407
00:32:43,252 --> 00:32:45,880
вҖӘIf we civil servants
вҖӘwant to live long enough

408
00:32:45,964 --> 00:32:48,549
вҖӘto claim a pension,
вҖӘwe need to watch our health.

409
00:32:48,633 --> 00:32:51,803
вҖӘExactly. To stay healthy,
вҖӘwe must eat food that's good for us.

410
00:32:51,886 --> 00:32:55,014
<i>вҖӘ-вҖҰpro golfer Park Seung-jae</i>
вҖӘ-Mr. Ma. The omakase nearbyвҖҰ

411
00:32:55,098 --> 00:32:58,226
<i>вҖӘwill compete</i>
<i>вҖӘin the Astra Championship this week.</i>

412
00:32:58,309 --> 00:33:03,940
<i>вҖӘHe was named as a suspect</i>
<i>вҖӘin </i><i>вҖӘthe </i><i>вҖӘmurder </i><i>вҖӘof his late girlfriend,</i>

413
00:33:04,023 --> 00:33:06,609
<i>вҖӘ-but was found not guilty,</i>
вҖӘ-What?

414
00:33:06,693 --> 00:33:08,611
<i>вҖӘ-thereby clearing his name.</i>
вҖӘ-He went right back to playing golf?

415
00:33:08,695 --> 00:33:11,531
<i>вҖӘHe resumed training</i>
<i>вҖӘas soon as the verdict was announced,</i>

416
00:33:11,614 --> 00:33:14,367
<i>вҖӘ-and is determined to return toвҖҰ</i>
вҖӘ-Championship, my ass.

417
00:33:14,450 --> 00:33:18,079
вҖӘBe it a witness or an informant,
вҖӘI wish someone would come forward.

418
00:33:18,162 --> 00:33:20,331
<i>вҖӘвҖҰfocusing on improving his score.</i>

419
00:33:20,415 --> 00:33:22,625
<i>вҖӘAs a likely winner of the tournament,</i>
<i>вҖӘPark Seung-jae--</i>

420
00:34:24,896 --> 00:34:26,731
вҖӘROUND 8
вҖӘ5 SONGS WITH LOCATIONS IN THE TITLE

421
00:35:27,667 --> 00:35:29,252
вҖӘYou're hurting my eyes!

422
00:35:32,630 --> 00:35:36,592
вҖӘIf you want to fiddle with the zipper,
вҖӘjust do it all in one go.

423
00:35:36,676 --> 00:35:39,095
вҖӘYou scared me by going bit by bit.

424
00:35:39,178 --> 00:35:41,097
вҖӘEven better, just knock.

425
00:35:44,308 --> 00:35:47,937
вҖӘI put up a wall because I was tired.

426
00:35:48,020 --> 00:35:50,273
вҖӘI'm not discriminating between ghosts.

427
00:35:52,650 --> 00:35:53,609
вҖӘOkay, fine.

428
00:35:54,485 --> 00:35:56,195
вҖӘI'll go. I'm going.

429
00:35:56,821 --> 00:35:58,030
вҖӘSee? I'm off.

430
00:36:05,872 --> 00:36:09,167
вҖӘYou went to death's door and back.

431
00:36:10,668 --> 00:36:12,461
вҖӘDo as they ask, if you can.

432
00:36:12,545 --> 00:36:13,754
вҖӘHelp the ghosts.

433
00:36:14,422 --> 00:36:17,884
вҖӘDoing as they ask and helping them
вҖӘis the only thing

434
00:36:18,718 --> 00:36:20,052
вҖӘthat will keep you alive.

435
00:36:25,016 --> 00:36:26,851
вҖӘIt doesn't feel right to ignore her,

436
00:36:26,934 --> 00:36:28,811
вҖӘbut helping them would be a hassle.

437
00:36:33,107 --> 00:36:34,108
вҖӘLet's go already.

438
00:36:37,737 --> 00:36:39,655
вҖӘ-Can we please go home?
вҖӘ-Wait.

439
00:36:39,739 --> 00:36:42,158
вҖӘLet's have one more drink.
вҖӘJust for another hour.

440
00:36:42,241 --> 00:36:44,785
вҖӘ-Your wife will kill me.
вҖӘ-Just another hour.

441
00:36:44,869 --> 00:36:47,997
вҖӘShe won't kill you. I said I'd be late,

442
00:36:48,080 --> 00:36:50,166
вҖӘand she texted back saying she understood.

443
00:36:50,249 --> 00:36:52,293
вҖӘNo way! Your wife's not like that!

444
00:36:52,376 --> 00:36:54,337
вҖӘWhy don't you believe me?
вҖӘI'll show you the text.

445
00:36:54,420 --> 00:36:56,005
вҖӘ-No, that's fine.
вҖӘ-Don't bother.

446
00:36:56,088 --> 00:36:57,673
вҖӘNo, why don't you both come to my place?

447
00:36:57,757 --> 00:37:00,718
вҖӘYou haven't seen my wife in a while.

448
00:37:00,801 --> 00:37:02,970
вҖӘI'll say, "Honey, cook us something."

449
00:37:03,054 --> 00:37:05,264
вҖӘ-We saw her not that long ago.
вҖӘ-Oh, taxi!

450
00:37:05,348 --> 00:37:08,309
вҖӘ-Let's go for a third round.
вҖӘ-You need to go home.

451
00:37:08,809 --> 00:37:10,269
вҖӘ-Get in quick.
вҖӘ-Wait, IвҖҰ

452
00:37:10,353 --> 00:37:12,063
вҖӘ-I got slapped for coming alone.
вҖӘ-Fine.

453
00:37:12,146 --> 00:37:13,940
вҖӘ-No, you won't get slapped.
вҖӘ-Just get in.

454
00:37:14,023 --> 00:37:17,193
вҖӘ-Watch your head as you get in.
вҖӘ-You might never see me again.

455
00:37:17,276 --> 00:37:18,653
вҖӘ-Watch your head.
вҖӘ-But IвҖҰ

456
00:37:18,736 --> 00:37:20,363
вҖӘGo on home already.

457
00:37:20,446 --> 00:37:21,948
вҖӘ-Take him home.
вҖӘ-Wait!

458
00:37:22,031 --> 00:37:24,075
вҖӘ-Here's the taxi fare.
вҖӘ-Get in.

459
00:37:24,158 --> 00:37:26,035
вҖӘ-Get home safely.
вҖӘ-No, wait!

460
00:37:27,870 --> 00:37:28,871
вҖӘOh, goshвҖҰ

461
00:37:30,456 --> 00:37:31,624
вҖӘHe never knows when to stop.

462
00:37:34,460 --> 00:37:35,586
вҖӘMan, I'm exhausted.

463
00:37:45,429 --> 00:37:47,223
вҖӘ-Where are you going?
вҖӘ-I need to take a leak.

464
00:37:47,306 --> 00:37:49,767
вҖӘCome right back. We're leaving right away.

465
00:37:56,023 --> 00:37:57,024
вҖӘWhat should I get?

466
00:38:18,587 --> 00:38:20,172
вҖӘGive me a pack of those red cigarettes.

467
00:38:31,392 --> 00:38:33,811
вҖӘHey, can you move your head?

468
00:38:33,894 --> 00:38:36,981
вҖӘI'm trying to park
вҖӘand you're blocking my view.

469
00:38:44,322 --> 00:38:45,239
вҖӘIs that the car?

470
00:38:48,200 --> 00:38:49,952
вҖӘI'm not the police.

471
00:38:52,038 --> 00:38:54,040
вҖӘI can't exactly do anything.

472
00:39:14,685 --> 00:39:15,603
вҖӘWhat was that?

473
00:39:15,686 --> 00:39:16,687
вҖӘDamn it.

474
00:39:22,068 --> 00:39:23,486
вҖӘOh, come on.

475
00:39:25,279 --> 00:39:26,614
вҖӘ-Are you all right?
вҖӘ-Yes.

476
00:39:27,740 --> 00:39:28,824
вҖӘThose crazy bastards.

477
00:39:45,674 --> 00:39:46,675
вҖӘStep on it.

478
00:39:47,176 --> 00:39:48,427
вҖӘWho are you?

479
00:39:48,511 --> 00:39:51,013
вҖӘ-Why did you jump into my car?
вҖӘ-That was a hit-and-run.

480
00:39:51,097 --> 00:39:53,265
вҖӘI can help. Don't worry.

481
00:39:53,766 --> 00:39:56,060
вҖӘWhat makes you think I'm worried?

482
00:39:58,687 --> 00:39:59,522
вҖӘHuh?

483
00:40:00,439 --> 00:40:01,273
вҖӘWhat?

484
00:40:03,025 --> 00:40:04,151
вҖӘWhat are you doing here?

485
00:40:04,235 --> 00:40:07,071
вҖӘYou're the one who jumped in.
вҖӘThat was forced entry.

486
00:40:07,154 --> 00:40:09,532
вҖӘStart the car first. I'll help you.

487
00:40:09,615 --> 00:40:12,827
вҖӘWhy do you keep saying you'll help?

488
00:40:12,910 --> 00:40:14,954
вҖӘI'll take care of it,
вҖӘso get out of my car.

489
00:40:15,037 --> 00:40:17,581
вҖӘThose two looked suspicious, okay?

490
00:40:17,665 --> 00:40:19,417
вҖӘThey didn't just smell of alcohol.

491
00:40:19,500 --> 00:40:21,544
вҖӘIf they're that suspicious,
вҖӘfollow them in your own car.

492
00:40:21,627 --> 00:40:24,130
вҖӘI would if I could. I can't drive drunk!

493
00:40:25,047 --> 00:40:27,091
вҖӘI'm not some weirdo. Here.

494
00:40:27,174 --> 00:40:29,552
вҖӘTake a look. I'm a prosecutor.

495
00:40:29,635 --> 00:40:32,721
вҖӘPretend you're assisting in a case
вҖӘand start the car.

496
00:40:32,805 --> 00:40:34,932
вҖӘHurry! We might lose them!

497
00:40:35,433 --> 00:40:38,310
вҖӘThey're stuck at a red light
вҖӘat the intersection up ahead!

498
00:40:38,394 --> 00:40:39,603
вҖӘSays who?

499
00:40:42,648 --> 00:40:43,482
вҖӘDarn it.

500
00:40:51,782 --> 00:40:54,034
вҖӘHey, isn't that the car I reversed into?

501
00:40:56,537 --> 00:40:57,413
вҖӘYou were right.

502
00:40:57,496 --> 00:40:59,665
вҖӘ-Step on the gas.
вҖӘ-Damn it.

503
00:41:01,250 --> 00:41:03,335
вҖӘSee if you can turn left from here.

504
00:41:03,419 --> 00:41:05,838
вҖӘ-I know a shortcut.
вҖӘ-Okay.

505
00:41:05,921 --> 00:41:07,715
вҖӘTurning right from here.

506
00:41:07,798 --> 00:41:08,632
вҖӘWhat?

507
00:41:11,844 --> 00:41:15,014
вҖӘWhy did you turn right?
вҖӘI told you to turn left.

508
00:41:15,097 --> 00:41:17,266
вҖӘOkay, then turn right up there.

509
00:41:17,349 --> 00:41:19,268
вҖӘ-Where do I go now? Left?
вҖӘ-What?

510
00:41:23,355 --> 00:41:24,899
вҖӘDon't you hear me?

511
00:41:24,982 --> 00:41:26,859
вҖӘYou're sure, right?

512
00:41:26,942 --> 00:41:28,402
вҖӘA right turn, then left turn?

513
00:41:28,486 --> 00:41:31,447
вҖӘAre you serious?
вҖӘWhen did I say turn right then left?

514
00:41:31,530 --> 00:41:34,950
вҖӘI told you to turn left then right,
вҖӘor right then right again.

515
00:41:35,034 --> 00:41:36,577
вҖӘBe quiet, both of you!

516
00:41:37,077 --> 00:41:39,163
вҖӘI can't concentrate
вҖӘwith you both shouting!

517
00:41:52,593 --> 00:41:54,011
вҖӘWe lost them.

518
00:41:54,803 --> 00:41:57,890
вҖӘThere's no teamwork here, just sabotage.

519
00:41:58,474 --> 00:41:59,767
вҖӘWe're not a team.

520
00:42:02,394 --> 00:42:04,522
вҖӘWe haven't lost them completely.

521
00:42:04,605 --> 00:42:06,440
вҖӘIt's a straight road from here on out,

522
00:42:06,524 --> 00:42:09,068
вҖӘand there are shortcuts
вҖӘon the way, he says.

523
00:42:09,151 --> 00:42:10,945
вҖӘI say, I mean.

524
00:42:16,867 --> 00:42:18,035
вҖӘWho is she talking to?

525
00:42:29,421 --> 00:42:30,714
вҖӘThis roadвҖҰ

526
00:42:38,305 --> 00:42:41,433
<i>вҖӘYou must stay well away from women</i>
<i>вҖӘborn in the year of the Black Monkey.</i>

527
00:42:41,517 --> 00:42:42,351
<i>вҖӘAll right?</i>

528
00:42:53,946 --> 00:42:56,073
вҖӘThis feels more like a shortcut to hell.

529
00:43:10,546 --> 00:43:13,716
<i>вҖӘHey, could you be a bit more careful?</i>

530
00:43:13,799 --> 00:43:15,092
вҖӘYour drivingвҖҰ

531
00:43:30,566 --> 00:43:31,609
вҖӘThe punk's a pretty good tail.

532
00:43:57,926 --> 00:43:58,802
вҖӘGet ahead of them.

533
00:44:13,901 --> 00:44:15,235
вҖӘGet into the other lane.

534
00:44:28,165 --> 00:44:29,249
вҖӘStep on it.

535
00:44:29,333 --> 00:44:31,502
вҖӘ-How much?
вҖӘ-Until I say stop.

536
00:44:41,095 --> 00:44:41,929
вҖӘNow!

537
00:44:54,483 --> 00:44:55,567
вҖӘThat crazyвҖҰ

538
00:44:55,651 --> 00:44:57,444
вҖӘNice, we did it. High-five.

539
00:45:02,699 --> 00:45:03,826
вҖӘDamn it.

540
00:45:04,493 --> 00:45:06,370
вҖӘStay in the car with the doors locked.

541
00:45:08,580 --> 00:45:10,332
вҖӘHey, be careful.

542
00:45:16,922 --> 00:45:18,674
вҖӘBeing a thug is all about the gear.

543
00:45:19,425 --> 00:45:21,677
вҖӘYou don't just do hit-and-runs, do you?

544
00:45:21,760 --> 00:45:23,512
вҖӘYou look like you rob people,
вҖӘat the very least.

545
00:46:03,469 --> 00:46:06,972
вҖӘLet's have you pay
вҖӘfor what you did right away.

546
00:46:07,055 --> 00:46:08,056
вҖӘPrison is the place for you.

547
00:46:25,741 --> 00:46:28,494
вҖӘThat's right.
вҖӘFights are all about the gear.

548
00:46:32,080 --> 00:46:33,415
вҖӘLend me a hand?

549
00:47:15,666 --> 00:47:16,625
вҖӘWellвҖҰ

550
00:47:17,209 --> 00:47:19,962
вҖӘCall me if you need a witness
вҖӘto the hit-and-run.

551
00:47:21,296 --> 00:47:24,299
вҖӘWhy don't you finish
вҖӘyour official business first?

552
00:47:41,775 --> 00:47:42,609
вҖӘWhatвҖҰ

553
00:48:09,094 --> 00:48:09,970
вҖӘPlease, no!

554
00:48:29,823 --> 00:48:30,866
вҖӘGoodbye,

555
00:48:31,867 --> 00:48:32,701
вҖӘto a better place.

556
00:48:59,561 --> 00:49:01,813
вҖӘSo it wasn't about the hit-and-run?

557
00:49:11,948 --> 00:49:12,949
вҖӘThat's impossible.

558
00:50:01,164 --> 00:50:01,998
вҖӘWhat was that?

559
00:50:14,094 --> 00:50:15,721
вҖӘWho is she really?

560
00:50:17,180 --> 00:50:19,391
вҖӘShe's no ghost,
вҖӘbut she appears wherever I go.

561
00:50:34,364 --> 00:50:35,323
вҖӘWhat's wrong with this?

562
00:50:45,167 --> 00:50:46,001
вҖӘHuh?

563
00:50:55,385 --> 00:50:56,219
вҖӘWhat the heck?

564
00:51:01,767 --> 00:51:02,934
вҖӘWhat's going on?

565
00:51:19,534 --> 00:51:20,994
вҖӘHey, Mr. Ma.

566
00:51:27,334 --> 00:51:28,168
вҖӘWhat was that?

567
00:51:29,085 --> 00:51:30,545
вҖӘWhy am I even dreaming about her?

568
00:51:43,558 --> 00:51:45,352
вҖӘ-Morning.
вҖӘ-Hey.

569
00:51:46,228 --> 00:51:48,021
вҖӘ-Mr. Ma.
вҖӘ-Yes?

570
00:51:48,104 --> 00:51:51,900
вҖӘFor the missing taxi driver case,
вҖӘthe suspects were indicted for murder.

571
00:51:52,818 --> 00:51:54,277
вҖӘHow did you catch them?

572
00:51:55,111 --> 00:51:55,946
вҖӘWellвҖҰ

573
00:51:56,029 --> 00:51:57,489
вҖӘ-Huh?
вҖӘ-What? What are you doing here?

574
00:51:57,572 --> 00:51:58,615
вҖӘ-Turn left.
вҖӘ-Turning right.

575
00:51:59,574 --> 00:52:00,867
вҖӘ-Turn right up there.
<i>вҖӘ-Left?</i>

576
00:52:00,951 --> 00:52:01,785
<i>вҖӘWhat?</i>

577
00:52:08,667 --> 00:52:10,585
вҖӘWe caught them and that's what matters.

578
00:52:10,669 --> 00:52:13,839
вҖӘDo we have surveillance footage
вҖӘfor the Mt. Haewang body disposal case?

579
00:52:13,922 --> 00:52:16,132
вҖӘSomething about that
вҖӘhas been bothering me.

580
00:52:16,216 --> 00:52:17,217
вҖӘDo we have it yet?

581
00:52:17,968 --> 00:52:20,846
вҖӘAbout 30 minutes
вҖӘbefore the victim's phone was turned on,

582
00:52:20,929 --> 00:52:23,348
вҖӘsomeone placed a call
вҖӘfrom a nearby payphone.

583
00:52:24,349 --> 00:52:25,433
вҖӘOh, they sent it over.

584
00:52:27,018 --> 00:52:27,853
вҖӘThere.

585
00:52:28,812 --> 00:52:31,565
вҖӘ-We only have a back profile.
вҖӘ-Wait.

586
00:52:31,648 --> 00:52:32,524
вҖӘWhat is it?

587
00:52:32,607 --> 00:52:34,818
вҖӘThe sneakers. Can you zoom in on them?

588
00:52:37,612 --> 00:52:38,989
вҖӘI'd recognize them anywhere.

589
00:52:39,823 --> 00:52:41,157
вҖӘHow did they get a pair?

590
00:52:41,241 --> 00:52:42,951
вҖӘ-What pair?
вҖӘ-You don't know the brand?

591
00:52:43,034 --> 00:52:44,911
вҖӘThose cost a fortune.

592
00:52:44,995 --> 00:52:47,289
вҖӘHow expensive could a pair of sneakers be?

593
00:52:47,914 --> 00:52:49,958
вҖӘ-They cost at least ten million won.
вҖӘ-What?

594
00:52:52,168 --> 00:52:55,964
вҖӘThis model is a collaboration
вҖӘbetween Blenciaga and Nice.

595
00:52:56,047 --> 00:52:57,007
вҖӘLet me see.

596
00:52:57,090 --> 00:52:59,509
вҖӘF&F Black and White.

597
00:52:59,593 --> 00:53:00,886
вҖӘIt's the limited edition.

598
00:53:01,636 --> 00:53:04,222
вҖӘOnly three pairs were sold in Korea.

599
00:53:05,807 --> 00:53:07,642
вҖӘI think I've seen these somewhere.

600
00:53:07,726 --> 00:53:09,227
вҖӘYou can't have.

601
00:53:09,311 --> 00:53:11,980
вҖӘYou don't know anyone
вҖӘwho could afford those.

602
00:53:12,731 --> 00:53:14,649
вҖӘThen again,
вҖӘthere are lots of knockoffs too.

603
00:53:17,193 --> 00:53:18,778
вҖӘYour top looks like a knockoff.

604
00:53:19,738 --> 00:53:20,655
вҖӘWhat?

605
00:53:31,374 --> 00:53:34,127
вҖӘGosh, what a flashy building.

606
00:53:34,961 --> 00:53:38,256
<i>вҖӘI looked into the three people</i>
<i>вҖӘwho bought those sneakers.</i>

607
00:53:38,340 --> 00:53:41,092
вҖӘOne flew to the US last month.

608
00:53:41,927 --> 00:53:45,597
вҖӘAnother one was locked up
вҖӘsix months ago for fraud.

609
00:53:46,431 --> 00:53:47,807
вҖӘThe third and last one's a bitвҖҰ

610
00:53:48,391 --> 00:53:49,476
вҖӘA bit what?

611
00:53:49,559 --> 00:53:52,395
вҖӘThere's no point
вҖӘin even checking them out.

612
00:54:04,115 --> 00:54:05,283
<i>вҖӘHeiress to Reina Group,</i>

613
00:54:05,951 --> 00:54:07,911
<i>вҖӘthe nation's fifth-largest </i><i>вҖӘconglomerate,</i>

614
00:54:07,994 --> 00:54:11,456
<i>вҖӘand CEO of the most luxurious hotel</i>
<i>вҖӘin the country, Cheon Yeo-ri.</i>

615
00:54:13,458 --> 00:54:15,669
<i>вҖӘShe has a strong aversion</i>
<i>вҖӘto meeting people,</i>

616
00:54:15,752 --> 00:54:19,047
<i>вҖӘso she rarely sits in meetings</i>
<i>вҖӘor does media interviews.</i>

617
00:54:19,881 --> 00:54:23,093
<i>вҖӘOnly a few core hotel executives</i>
<i>вҖӘknow what she looks like.</i>

618
00:54:24,177 --> 00:54:27,138
<i>вҖӘSo Mr. Ma,</i>
<i>вҖӘif you go there without a warrant,</i>

619
00:54:27,222 --> 00:54:29,474
<i>вҖӘyou'll get turned away</i>
<i>вҖӘbefore you set eyes on her.</i>

620
00:54:35,647 --> 00:54:36,481
вҖӘHello.

621
00:54:36,564 --> 00:54:39,401
вҖӘI'm Prosecutor Ma Gang-uk from Seoul
вҖӘCentral District Prosecutors' Office.

622
00:54:39,484 --> 00:54:41,152
вҖӘI'd like to meet the CEO.

623
00:54:42,237 --> 00:54:45,031
вҖӘYou can't request
вҖӘa private meeting with her.

624
00:54:45,699 --> 00:54:47,075
вҖӘWhat do I have to do then?

625
00:54:47,158 --> 00:54:49,995
вҖӘIf you send an official request
вҖӘto the secretary's office,

626
00:54:50,078 --> 00:54:52,414
вҖӘthey'll review it and get back to you.

627
00:54:59,671 --> 00:55:00,505
вҖӘThank you.

628
00:55:10,432 --> 00:55:13,977
вҖӘWe extend a warm welcome from Reina.

629
00:55:14,060 --> 00:55:15,437
вҖӘ-Hello.
вҖӘ-Hello.

630
00:55:27,115 --> 00:55:28,867
вҖӘDid you see a woman in a checkered outfit?

631
00:55:28,950 --> 00:55:29,868
вҖӘNo?

632
00:55:40,295 --> 00:55:42,255
вҖӘWhy is he coming after me?

633
00:55:42,338 --> 00:55:43,715
вҖӘWhat is this about?

634
00:55:47,927 --> 00:55:50,305
вҖӘShe's so darn fast. Jeez.

635
00:55:50,388 --> 00:55:51,514
вҖӘExcuse me?

636
00:55:53,391 --> 00:55:54,684
вҖӘHello?

637
00:56:01,232 --> 00:56:02,067
вҖӘWait up!

638
00:56:06,404 --> 00:56:08,114
вҖӘWill you justвҖҰ

639
00:56:09,115 --> 00:56:10,617
вҖӘWhat theвҖҰ Are you serious?

640
00:56:15,413 --> 00:56:17,707
вҖӘWhy is this hotel so massive?

641
00:56:17,791 --> 00:56:19,459
вҖӘHey, wait. Can we just talk?

642
00:56:21,127 --> 00:56:22,378
вҖӘWhy are there so many stairs?

643
00:56:38,978 --> 00:56:39,896
вҖӘWhere'd she go?

644
00:56:40,855 --> 00:56:43,066
вҖӘHe won't follow me in here, will he?

645
00:56:44,025 --> 00:56:45,151
вҖӘWhat's going on?

646
00:57:07,423 --> 00:57:09,843
<i>вҖӘWhy does he keep appearing wherever I go?</i>

647
00:57:09,926 --> 00:57:11,302
<i>вҖӘIs he stalking me?</i>

648
00:57:12,554 --> 00:57:13,388
вҖӘWhere did she go?

649
00:57:16,975 --> 00:57:18,685
вҖӘWhy were you out so late?

650
00:57:18,768 --> 00:57:20,562
вҖӘI'm just asking.

651
00:57:20,645 --> 00:57:22,689
вҖӘI envy you for having plans after work.

652
00:57:22,772 --> 00:57:26,025
вҖӘOh, don't worry. It wasn't a guy, okay?

653
00:57:26,109 --> 00:57:28,027
вҖӘYou should date someone.

654
00:57:28,111 --> 00:57:29,195
вҖӘWill you set me up?

655
00:57:29,279 --> 00:57:31,364
<i>вҖӘWhat? He didn't leave?</i>

656
00:57:34,075 --> 00:57:35,994
вҖӘDid you see Cheon Yeo-ri yesterday?

657
00:57:36,077 --> 00:57:37,954
вҖӘ"Stop. Maintain your distance."

658
00:57:38,746 --> 00:57:41,541
вҖӘ-You sound just like her.
вҖӘ-Don't I?

659
00:57:41,624 --> 00:57:44,627
вҖӘWas she always so hard to be around?

660
00:57:44,711 --> 00:57:48,173
вҖӘYeah, I've been here for five years
вҖӘand she was like that then too.

661
00:57:48,756 --> 00:57:51,176
вҖӘShe ignored a kid
вҖӘwho fell right in front of her.

662
00:57:51,259 --> 00:57:53,887
вҖӘShe ignores everything and everyone.

663
00:57:53,970 --> 00:57:56,848
вҖӘIs she a germaphobe?
вҖӘShe's always wearing gloves.

664
00:57:57,432 --> 00:58:00,226
вҖӘWasn't she pretending to be
вҖӘa European crown princess?

665
00:58:01,186 --> 00:58:02,604
вҖӘShe's the worst.

666
00:58:02,687 --> 00:58:05,398
вҖӘI wish ghosts would drag away
вҖӘentitled people like her--

667
00:58:08,401 --> 00:58:10,195
вҖӘMy gosh. Ms. Cheon.

668
00:58:11,654 --> 00:58:12,489
вҖӘ"Ms. Cheon"?

669
00:58:15,408 --> 00:58:16,451
вҖӘ-Oh, no.
вҖӘ-What do we do?

670
00:58:24,834 --> 00:58:25,793
вҖӘOh, my legs.

671
00:58:43,770 --> 00:58:45,813
вҖӘWhat is he doing here?

672
00:58:46,606 --> 00:58:48,191
вҖӘWhy do we keep crossing paths?

673
00:58:51,402 --> 00:58:52,445
вҖӘWhere am I?

674
00:58:55,949 --> 00:58:58,117
вҖӘI'm pretty sure she went this way.

675
00:59:03,248 --> 00:59:04,123
вҖӘCEO'S OFFICE

676
00:59:06,876 --> 00:59:07,710
вҖӘHello?

677
00:59:10,380 --> 00:59:11,214
вҖӘNo one's here.

678
00:59:12,549 --> 00:59:13,383
вҖӘWhat the heck?

679
01:00:53,274 --> 01:00:55,985
вҖӘSPOOKY IN LOVE

680
01:00:56,069 --> 01:01:00,031
<i>вҖӘPark Seung-jae sunk </i><i>вҖӘthrilling </i><i>вҖӘshot</i>
<i>вҖӘafter </i><i>вҖӘshot </i><i>вҖӘat the championship</i>

681
01:01:00,114 --> 01:01:02,784
<i>вҖӘand is now top of the leaderboard</i>
<i>вҖӘin the third round.</i>

682
01:01:02,867 --> 01:01:05,036
<i>вҖӘWe must find something</i>
<i>вҖӘwe might have overlooked.</i>

683
01:01:05,119 --> 01:01:07,080
<i>вҖӘSomething to overturn the verdict</i>
<i>вҖӘin the second trial.</i>

684
01:01:07,163 --> 01:01:08,039
<i>вҖӘA smoking gun.</i>

685
01:01:08,122 --> 01:01:09,874
<i>вҖӘThe truth is, Jang Eun-ju</i>

686
01:01:09,957 --> 01:01:11,876
<i>вҖӘcame to our hotel before she went missing.</i>

687
01:01:11,959 --> 01:01:13,252
вҖӘCould this be a coincidence?

688
01:01:13,878 --> 01:01:15,254
вҖӘLet's go for a three-way encounter.

689
01:01:15,338 --> 01:01:18,549
<i>вҖӘSo you're saying</i>
<i>вҖӘJang Eun-ju is coming here?</i>

690
01:01:20,510 --> 01:01:21,344
<i>вҖӘDid we make contact?</i>

691
01:01:21,427 --> 01:01:23,096
<i>вҖӘWhat then? That would be a disaster.</i>

692
01:01:23,179 --> 01:01:24,180
вҖӘExcuse me.

693
01:01:24,263 --> 01:01:26,432
вҖӘDid you and IвҖҰ

694
01:01:26,516 --> 01:01:28,059
вҖӘYou're not at all my type.

695
01:01:29,268 --> 01:01:31,479
<i>вҖӘWho cares if he sees ghosts or not?</i>

696
01:01:39,237 --> 01:01:44,242
вҖӘSubtitle translation by: Jennifer Jean Lim
